go to your clinic or dental clinic and wait for your appointment.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We will do our best for you to see the doctor at your appointment. In the event of any delay, our staff will inform you of the matter, if you arrive without an appointment, patients who have pre-booked appointments will be given priority.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Book patient follow-up appointments</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If your condition requires booking an additional appointment for a review with the specialist doctor, the nurse will record the date of the next appointment on the appointment card based on the instructions of the attending physician. Therefore, you have to go with this card to the reception desk to complete the appointment reservation procedures.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Cancel the appointment</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There is usually a waiting list for the names of patients who need to make an appointment in the outpatient setting. Therefore, if you are unable to attend your appointment, it is imperative that you contact us at least two days before the date of your appointment so that we can give your appointment to another patient.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Checks and procedures</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The attending physician may ask you to perform additional examinations and procedures immediately after the medical appointment, and the nurse will direct you to the appropriate department where you can perform the required examinations.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If these examinations are urgent, you will be asked after completing these examinations to return again to the reception desk in the clinic you were in, and the attending doctor will search the results of these examinations with you on the same day, and if these tests are not urgent, the results of the tests will be deposited in your file The doctor will discuss these results with you when you meet with you at the next appointment.</span></p>','2021-01-01 09:03:38','2021-01-01 09:03:38'),(549,'patient_guids','title',8,'en',' Planning your Hospital Stay','2021-01-01 09:08:07','2021-01-01 09:08:07'),(550,'patient_guids','content',8,'en','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Before starting the admission procedures, you will receive all necessary information related to your stay in the hospital from your doctor, the nurse assigned to care for you, or the patient educator. We at Al-Moosa Hospital take care of the details related to the stay of patients in the hospital.</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-bcd27e58-7fff-f2c1-f6dd-b04abc3e196d\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You must bring all medical documents and medicines that you take (in their original packages) when you arrive at the hospital, as soon as you enter the hospital, the hospital care team can provide you with the prescribed treatments.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">As for clothing or personal items; Al Moosa Hospital will provide the following: </span></span></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sleepwear for men and women and the patient can wear the clothes he prefers. </span></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Slippers or light shoes.</span></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Toothbrush, toothpaste, deodorant, hairbrush, towel, and tissues.</span></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Books and magazines.</span></span></span></li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 09:08:07','2021-01-01 09:08:07'),(551,'patient_guids','title',9,'en',' Preparing for a Procedure','2021-01-01 09:10:02','2021-01-01 09:10:02'),(552,'patient_guids','content',9,'en','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Once you and your doctor decide that surgery is necessary, you will need to know what to expect from the surgery and create a treatment plan for the best results afterward.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Mental and physical preparation for surgery is a necessary step towards successful outcomes. Understanding the surgery and knowing your role in it will help you recover more quickly and avoid many problems.</span></p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-6d423bfa-7fff-c0e9-9965-68d5294a4ef1\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">At Al Moosa Hospital we give great attention to this part, as it is an essential part of the correct healthcare process.</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br /><br /></strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Important advice before medical procedures:</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Before surgery, your doctor will perform a complete physical examination to make sure there are no conditions that might interfere with the surgery or the results. He usually performs routine tests, such as blood tests and X-rays, a week before any major surgery.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Discuss with your doctor and family physician any medications you are taking to find out which ones you should refrain from before surgery.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Discuss options for preparing for a potential blood transfusion with your doctors, such as blood donation, medical interventions, and other treatments, before surgery.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you are overweight, losing weight before surgery can help reduce stress on the new joint. However, you must not follow a diet during the month before the surgery.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you are taking aspirin, anti-inflammatory drugs, warfarin, or any medications that increase the risk of bleeding, you should stop them a week before surgery to reduce bleeding.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you smoke, you should quit or reduce smoking to reduce the risks of surgery and improve healing and recovery.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Treat any problems with the teeth, gums, bladder, or bowel before surgery to reduce the risk of infection later.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Eat a balanced diet, with a daily multivitamin and iron supplements.</span></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br /><br /><br /></strong></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Inform your surgeon of any infections you have. Surgery cannot be performed until the infections are completely gone.</span></li>\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 09:10:02','2021-01-01 09:10:02'),(553,'patient_guids','title',10,'en','Patient Complains','2021-01-01 09:11:19','2021-01-01 09:11:19'),(554,'patient_guids','content',10,'en','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Complaints submitted by the patient are one of the most important methods of measuring and improving the beneficiaries\' experience of health services at Al-Mousa Specialist Hospital. And applications in quality, patient safety, and patient experience.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.295; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The patient can submit any inquiry, suggestion, or complaint through the Patient Relations Office (Office 1423) Tel: 0552952660</span></p>','2021-01-01 09:11:19','2021-01-01 09:11:19'),(555,'patient_guids','title',11,'en',' Waiting Areas','2021-01-01 09:16:12','2021-01-01 09:16:12'),(556,'patient_guids','content',11,'en','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We, at Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital, care about the patient and those who care for him as well, so if one of them is undergoing a medical procedure inside the hospital, you can wait in the places that have been designated for rest, as in one of the waiting centers, a place has been allocated for men and another for women.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">It is worth noting that each lounge provides comfortable areas for sitting and rest, television, and an open, high-speed Internet.</span></p>','2021-01-01 09:16:12','2021-01-01 09:16:12'),(557,'patient_guids','title',12,'en','Interpreter Services','2021-01-01 09:19:45','2021-01-01 09:19:45'),(558,'patient_guids','content',12,'en','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The little details set us apart!</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If the language is a hindrance or you have difficulty understanding medical instructions inside Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital, or you need medical information in a language other than Arabic, we provide interpretation services for you and your loved ones, free instant translation and high quality, to reach an integrated medical service without any barriers.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Available Arabic translations: English - Russian - Tagalog - Urdu - Hindi - Malayalam - Portuguese - Bangladeshi - Kashmiri - Italian - French.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">All Al Moosa Hospital staff can help you arrange language services</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">You can also call the interpreter services office at 0135369666 (1272-1423).</span></p>','2021-01-01 09:19:45','2021-01-01 09:19:45'),(559,'patient_guids','title',13,'en','Mosques','2021-01-01 09:20:51','2021-01-01 09:20:51'),(560,'patient_guids','content',13,'en','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There are two mosques within Al Moosa Specialist Hospital:</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font