amily: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Osteopathic osteomyelitis to repair the scoliosis of the tibia, femur, and neck of the femur.</span></p>','2021-01-01 17:35:54','2021-01-01 17:35:54'),(694,'service_section_items','title',21,'en','Sports Injuries Unit','2021-01-01 17:37:39','2021-01-01 17:37:39'),(695,'service_section_items','content',21,'en','<p>The Sports Injuries Unit within the Medical and Orthopedic Center within the Almoosa Specialist Center has a good reputation among the sports community by virtue of its success in its experience with the Al-Fatah Model Club as it provided the club with medical care at the highest level.</p>\n<p>Among the services provided by the unit:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Treatment of all sports injuries cases such as anterior and posterior cruciate ligaments and collateral ligaments.</li>\n<li>Treatment of meniscus by minimally invasive surgery.</li>\n<li>The use of laparoscopic surgery in the treatment of shoulder muscle cuts.</li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 17:37:39','2021-03-11 12:57:17'),(696,'service_section_items','title',22,'en','Physiotherapy Unit','2021-01-01 17:39:16','2021-01-01 17:39:16'),(697,'service_section_items','content',22,'en','<p>Physical therapy and follow-up after orthopedic injuries and the subsequent surgical or non-surgical interventions are important and necessary to reach the optimal state and reach the largest possible degree of the basic functions of the affected organ, any defect in physical therapy after injury may lead to negative consequences for the patient after Processes.</p>\n<p>Therefore, we at the Orthopedic Center take care of the patient\'s physical therapy and strive to reach the best possible quality and help speed up the patient\'s recovery and the affected organs return to their normal function through some distinguished services, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assessment of the physical ability to engage in physical activity or exercise.</li>\n<li>A comprehensive health check-up before a sporting activity or exercise. - Rehabilitation of sports injuries.</li>\n<li>Provide medical consultations on exercise and weight loss.</li>\n<li>Medical consultations about physical activity or exercise for the prevention and treatment of specific conditions such as diabetes and hypertension.</li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 17:39:16','2021-01-08 17:05:19'),(698,'service_section_items','title',23,'en','Why the orthopedic center at Al-Moosa Hospital?','2021-01-01 17:41:06','2021-01-01 17:41:06'),(699,'service_section_items','content',23,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Experience, care, and modern means in one place, rapid handling of emergency cases, and trained medical staff at the highest level are the most prominent features of the Orthopedic Surgery and Medicine Center within Al Mousa Specialist Hospital!</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In addition, there are many features within the center that we have provided for the convenience of the hospital\'s visitors, and certainly in our endeavor to raise the quality of our services provided, these features include:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; The latest diagnostic methods of magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and computed tomography.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; Detecting with the utmost accuracy the proportion of osteoporosis and vitamin \"D\".</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; Excellence in providing optimal treatment for sports injuries, as the center deals with players in professional clubs registered in the Saudi Sports Federation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; The use of laparoscopic surgery in the treatment of sports injuries and shoulder.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; Treatment of friction and stiffness of the knee, pelvis, and shoulder joints, with the latest recommendations of joint replacement surgery.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; Treating all types of fractures with the latest and best types of fixatives.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; Accurate diagnosis within the center, where we provide the optimal treatment for intractable deformities and bacterial infections of the bones.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull; We provide the necessary rehabilitation to our patients as we take care of them by providing them with appropriate physical therapy services, to fully recover and return the affected organs to their normal state.</span></p>','2021-01-01 17:41:06','2021-01-01 17:41:06'),(700,'service_sections','title',20,'en','Clinics and Services','2021-01-01 17:42:43','2021-01-01 17:42:43'),(701,'service_sections','title',21,'en','Vision Correction Unit by Intralasik','2021-01-01 17:43:33','2021-01-01 17:43:33'),(702,'service_sections','title',22,'en','Laser and Retinal Surgery','2021-01-01 17:45:33','2021-01-01 17:45:33'),(703,'service_sections','title',23,'en','Keratoconus Treatment and Surgeries','2021-01-01 17:46:55','2021-01-01 17:46:55'),(704,'service_sections','title',24,'en','White Water Treatment and Surgery','2021-01-01 17:48:09','2021-01-01 17:48:09'),(705,'service_sections','title',25,'en','Corrective Lens Implantation','2021-01-01 17:48:50','2021-01-01 17:48:50'),(706,'service_sections','title',26,'en','Pediatric Eye Surgery and Strabismus Correction','2021-01-01 17:50:07','2021-01-01 17:50:07'),(707,'service_sections','title',27,'en','Dacryocystorhinostomy (DCR-Dacryocystorhinostomy) Operations Through The Nose Without External Surgery','2021-01-01 17:51:13','2021-01-01 17:51:13'),(708,'service_sections','title',28,'en','Capabilities and Equipment','2021-01-01 17:52:08','2021-01-01 17:52:08'),(709,'service_section_items','title',24,'en','Clinics and Services','2021-01-01 17:55:11','2021-01-01 17:55:11'),(710,'service_section_items','content',24,'en','<p>The center is equipped with the latest medical devices and the most skilled ophthalmologists and surgeons in the Kingdom and equipped with six fully-equipped clinics with the latest medical units related to ophthalmology, two rooms for optics and prescription of eyeglasses required for some patients\' ailments and deviations, and four examination rooms equipped with the latest investigations in an environment that adheres to the utmost sterilization And safety to maintain the safety of the eyes and prevent the spread of infectious diseases, by virtue of the sensitivity of handling the eyes.</p>','2021-01-01 17:55:11','2021-01-08 17:05:41'),(711,'service_section_items','title',25,'en','Vision Correction Unit by Intralasik','2021-01-01 18:02:11','2021-01-01 18:02:11'),(712,'service_section_items','content',25,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The Femto LASIK vision correction process is one of the modern techniques used internationally in the treatment of vision defects by laser, and it is considered one of the qualitative leaps in the process of correcting vision defects as it uses laser beams completely without the presence of any surgical scalpel or surgical blade in the process.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Features of the Intralasek process:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Without any pain.</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">High speed in the process.</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Without a scalpel, making it safe and accurate.</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">No need for general anesthesia, only local anesthesia.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The patient does not put a cover on the eye after the operation, so he can practice his normal life immediately after the operation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">We at Al Moosa Specialist Center always use the latest devices in our operations and use the latest tried and proven medical technologies internationally, so we are keen to use the German SCHWIND device, which is distinguished from the rest of the devices by the following:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The ability to perform the operation without touching the eye, and without using the surgical scalpel, which is called TRANS PRK technology.</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The device is equipped with the fastest eye movement tracking system during the application of the laser, to obtain the highest possible accuracy.</span></li>\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The high speed of the device, which shortens the operation time.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">When do we use Intralasek operations?</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Cases of myopia</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Cases of deviation</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Cases of farsightedness</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">When cannot the vision correction operation be used?</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Unfortunately, sometimes, vision correction operations cannot be performed due to some of the symptoms that the patient has, which may be a barrier to the success of the operation or a reason to reduce its success rate.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>However, do not worry! We in the Eye Center of Almoosa Specialist Hospital treat these symptoms, and then we can accomplish this process easier, with a high success rate and with extreme accuracy.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Cases where vision correction operations cannot be used for them:</span></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Patients with cataracts in the eyes.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Patients infected with the herpes virus.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Patients with severe dry eyes.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Pregnant women due to hormonal changes that affect degrees of vision.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Advice after femtolasek vision correction</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Because follow-up after operations is an integral part of our medical procedures that cannot be dispensed with, which must be taken care of and provide sound medical advice to the patient, in order to reach the highest possible success rate after the operation, so we advise you after the Intralasek procedure the following things:</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Refrain from scratching the eye.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Avoid getting water into the eyes 3 days after the operation.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Stay away from any heat source that may lead to dry eyes, such as the oven or any other heat source.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Use moisturizing drops prescribed by a doctor to avoid dry eyes.</span></li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 18:02:11','2021-03-11 12:57:37'),(713,'service_section_items','title',26,'en','Laser and Retinal Surgery','2021-01-01 18:04:40','2021-01-01 18:04:40'),(714,'service_section_items','content',26,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In the case of diabetic retinopathy and retinal vein occlusion, the doctors of the Eye Center inside Almoosa Specialist Hospital resort to treating the damage to the retina from tearing or otherwise with laser, achieving impressive results and a high success rate.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In addition, the center provides many benefits and services with a high degree of accuracy and professionalism, such as:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Laser examination and treatment for cases of retinopathy of prematurity (babies born less than 9 months pregnant).</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Vitreous injection for treating visual center infiltration for diabetics.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Macular degeneration associated with age.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Retinal vein occlusion.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Retinal detachment repair.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Retinal fixation using surgical gas.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Vitrectomy for retinal detachment, vitreous hemorrhage, and advanced diabetic retinopathy.</span></li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 18:04:40','2021-03-11 12:57:50'),(715,'service_section_items','title',27,'en','Corneal Surgery and Treatment','2021-01-01 18:08:54','2021-01-01 18:08:54'),(716,'service_section_items','content',27,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The cornea is one of the most important parts of the eye, as it is the transparent front part of the eye through which light enters the eye, and its problems are common among people.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In some cases that may be related to hereditary diseases or with aging or after surgical intervention of the eye, weakness or atrophy of the eye may occur, which leads to it stops working and severe blurry vision. Which may force doctors to surgical intervention in a process called corneal transplantation, which leads to a significant and clear change in the patient.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In the past, corneal transplantation was performed by transplanting all three layers of the cornea, which required sewing the cornea in a circular motion with about 16 surgical stitches, and after a full year of transplantation, it is removed, while the patient does not regain vision completely until after the stitches are completely removed, That is, a year after the operation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Recently, there has been a remarkable development in corneal transplantation operations, whereby the inner layer of the cornea is replaced only by a healthy layer taken from an intact cornea (donated after death), without the need to replace the entire layers of the cornea, and the lining of the cornea is fixed inside the eye by air without the need for surgical sutures. Therefore, this type of corneal transplant can be described as follows:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Replacing the inner layer of the cornea only without any other additives, which gives a very accurate improvement in the eyesight after the operation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Vision improved rapidly, often within several days after the operation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>No surgical stitches.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Sometimes the body may reject the nucleus keratoplasty and treat it as a foreign body, which is known as immune rejection:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In this type of surgery, the incidence of immune rejection is very low (less than 1%) and it is much less than the percentage of immune rejection in cases of transplantation of entire corneal layers (10-20%).</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Usually dealing with the cornea requires a high degree of accuracy and medical knowledge to reach satisfactory results. We at the Eye Center at Musa Specialist Hospital have assigned a special department within the center, and we are constantly keen to provide high-quality medical services for the cornea by using the latest medical equipment, such as:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">O <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">corneal transplantation operations in all its methods:</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt 1.0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>PKP full-thickness cornea transplant</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt 1.0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&bull;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Partial-thickness DALK cornea transplant.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt 1.0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&middot;<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>DMEK / DSAEK keratoplasty.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">O <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Keratoconus treatment and surgeries</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Transplantation of corneal rings to treat Keratoconus using a femtosecond laser device, which gives better and more accurate results than the traditional surgical method of implanting the rings.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Corneal phototherapy (cross-linking) to stop the development of Keratoconus, an eye disease in which the cornea gradually curves from an asymmetrical dome shape to an asymmetric cone-like shape.</span></p>','2021-01-01 18:08:54','2021-01-08 17:08:25'),(717,'service_section_items','title',28,'en','White Water Treatment and Surgery','2021-01-01 18:10:15','2021-01-01 18:10:15'),(718,'service_section_items','content',28,'en','<p>Cataract surgeries by phaco-method - a new technique to get rid of the affected lens with cataract, by dissolving the lens, then withdrawing the fluid and replacing it with a physiological fluid, then installing the replacement lens without surgical stitches - this method is characterized by a rapid improvement in vision after the operation and often seen The patient is completely evident on the second day after the operation.</p>','2021-01-01 18:10:15','2021-01-08 16:56:32'),(719,'service_section_items','title',29,'en',' Corrective Lens Implantation','2021-01-01 18:13:29','2021-01-01 18:13:29'),(720,'service_section_items','content',29,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Some disease conditions cannot be treated with laser, so doctors resort to treating them using corrective lens implants to treat refractive defects and lens damage, including:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">ICL lenses: Made of high-quality material specially designed for implantation directly in front of the natural lens, and can be used in the treatment of long or short-sightedness.</span></li>\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\n<li><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Multifocal lenses: which help the patient to look near and far together without using glasses after the multifocal procedure.</span></li>\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\n<li><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Astigmatism lenses: which are used to create a clear image on the retina and improve vision.</span></li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 18:13:29','2021-01-08 16:56:52'),(721,'service_section_items','title',30,'en','Pediatric Eye Surgery and Strabismus Correction','2021-01-01 18:16:06','2021-01-01 18:16:06'),(722,'service_section_items','content',30,'en','<p>Eye problems and squint are common problems in children, which require intervention at an early age in order to control the problems as much as possible, raise the rate of healing, and return of the eyes to normal.</p>\n<p>In many cases, the treatment of strabismus depends on the degree of disease progression in the condition, so parents should realize that treatment in the form of glasses, eye drops, exercises, or eye muscle surgery, is effective when it is taken early in the child\'s development, Whereas when the strabismus condition progresses in the child, doctors may resort to a surgical solution.</p>\n<p>It is possible to perform squint repair operations within the Eye Center at Almoosa Specialist Hospital through some modern medical interventions, such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Weakening of some of the oculomotor muscles: such as weakening the internal rectus muscle in cases of the amygdala by returning it back a certain distance according to the measured angle of strabismus, or weakening the external rectus muscle in cases of lateral strabismus by returning it back.</li>\n<li>Strengthening some of the muscles that move the eye: such as removing part of the muscle to shorten it or bend the muscle, and it is also used for the muscles to be strengthened, such as strengthening the external rectus muscle in some cases of medial strabismus.</li>\n<li>Changing the course of some muscles: such as changing the course of the lower oblique muscle in some vertical strabismus repairs.</li>\n</ul>','2021-01-01 18:16:06','2021-03-11 12:58:14'),(723,'service_section_items','title',31,'en','Dacryocystorhinostomy (DCR-Dacryocystorhinostomy) Operations Through The Nose Without External Surgery','2021-01-01 18:18:04','2021-01-01 18:18:04'),(724,'service_section_items','content',31,'en','<p>This operation aims to form a new tear duct between the eye and the nose when a blockage occurs in the original tear duct. In the event of a blockage or narrowing of the normal tear duct, the patient may suffer from swelling around the eye and frequent infections within it.</p>\n<p>During the process of widening the tear duct, the tear ducts are opened so that the tears are diverted through the nose, and the operation is performed laparoscopically, which is a minimally invasive procedure that aims to open the blocked tear ducts.</p>\n<p>This process is very similar to the process of expanding the tear duct externally, except that it does not require a surgical incision and does not leave a scar or a trace on the skin.</p>','2021-01-01 18:18:04','2021-01-08 16:59:20'),(725,'service_section_items','title',32,'en','Capabilities and Equipment','2021-01-01 18:19:22','2021-01-01 18:19:22'),(726,'service_section_items','content',32,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">In the Eye Center at Almoosa Specialist Hospital, we are keen to keep abreast of modern medical technologies, and to provide the center with the latest findings in medical science in terms of equipment, in addition to a team of doctors and technicians equipped with knowledge and competence to work on them and analyze the results shown from them, and later to determine the methods of treatment and follow-up and prescribe appropriate drugs Case.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The most important modern medical devices in the eye center at Al Moosa Specialist Hospital and their uses:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Corneal topography device, which is used to determine the suitability of the cornea for laser vision correction operations.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Eye print device, which is used to measure deviations inside the eye and determine the identity of the patient, where a fingerprint of the cornea is taken, then the information is transferred to the laser vision correction device to apply laser strikes to specific places on the surface of the cornea in order to modify the shape of the cornea and reach the ideal shape Which gives the best acuity of eyesight.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">A device for measuring the number and shape of corneal lining cells (specular microscope: </span>It is the newest and most accurate device of its kind in the region, which is used before cataract operations to determine the ability of the cornea to withstand the operation, thus preventing weakness in the cornea after the cataract operation and the need for corneal transplantation, in addition to using the device in following up cases after corneal transplantation operations.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Optical Coherence Tomography device - OTC: It is a non-invasive imaging technology used to obtain high-resolution cross-sectional images of the retina.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Fluorescein Angiography Device.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">A visual field examination device.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">A device for measuring the power of the lens that is to be implanted inside the eye.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Echo device to examine the posterior sections of the eye.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Argon laser device, which is used to treat some retinopathies, and in some cases it, is used to prevent the deterioration of the condition of the eye and to maintain its normal functions as much as possible.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">YAG laser, which is used for a simple medical procedure that does not require anesthesia, is painless and takes only 5-10 minutes. It is used to perform iris biopsy, posterior capsule biopsy, and treat blurry vision.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The Eye Center crews at Al-Moosa Specialist Hospital take good care of your eyes. Our teams are known for their high efficiency, long experience, and full care for patient comfort.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>In addition to our modern equipment that keeps pace with the latest in modern medical science, so do not hesitate to visit us and take reliable medical advice.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Always make sure that our attention to simple details is what makes Almoosa Specialist Hospital special!</span></p>','2021-01-01 18:19:22','2021-03-11 12:58:28'),(727,'service_sections','title',29,'en','Laparoscopic Gastric Bypass Surgery','2021-01-01 18:21:37','2021-01-01 18:21:37'),(728,'service_sections','title',30,'en','Laparoscopic Sleeve Gastrectomy','2021-01-01 18:22:59','2021-01-01 18:22:59'),(729,'service_sections','title',31,'en','Converting from Sleeve Gastrectomy to Laparoscopic Graft','2021-01-01 18:24:00','2021-01-01 18:24:00'),(730,'service_sections','title',32,'en','Removing a stomach belt (ring) and converting to a sleeve gastrectomy or bypass','2021-01-01 18:24:46','2021-01-01 18:24:46'),(731,'service_section_items','title',33,'en','Laparoscopic Gastric Bypass Surgery','2021-01-01 18:26:01','2021-01-01 18:26:01'),(732,'service_section_items','content',33,'en','<p>It is one of the most popular and effective procedures in the treatment of obesity, which helps to lose weight effectively by making some adjustments to the process of digestion and absorption of food through the stomach and intestine, this process does not require any surgical intervention.</p>','2021-01-01 18:26:01','2021-01-08 17:01:04'),(733,'service_section_items','title',34,'en','Laparoscopic sleeve gastrectomy','2021-01-01 18:27:05','2021-01-01 18:27:05'),(734,'service_section_items','content',34,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 8.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">&nbsp;It is the most requested medical procedure that may be used to treat obesity and other matters such as malignant tumors.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt .5in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Some studies indicate that the gastric sleeve operation leads to a loss of 33% of a person\'s weight in the first three months of the operat