ot through curative catheters. We use the balloon to open and expand the arteries, with the use of arterial stents, to work on healing the diabetic foot, which avoids amputation.</p>','2021-01-01 21:35:36','2021-01-08 16:30:50'),(826,'service_section_items','title',65,'en','Intravascular angioplasty','2021-01-01 21:36:49','2021-01-01 21:36:49'),(827,'service_section_items','content',65,'en','<p>Interventional catheterization represents a revolution in the field of vascular surgery; we use it in the treatment of clogged arteries of the extremities, through which diagnostic and therapeutic examinations are performed. Using them, we avoid surgical intervention, as they do not need general anesthesia, and the patient can leave the hospital on the same day, or the next day at the latest in most cases.</p>\n<p>For the first time in the region, we used carbon dioxide gas instead of dye in the diagnosis and treatment of these conditions, to restore the damage to the kidneys and the heart from the use of dye in kidney failure.</p>\n<p>This is a glimmer of hope for these patients, as the use of traditional dye carries a risk of chronic kidney failure and requires continuous dialysis.</p>','2021-01-01 21:36:49','2021-01-08 16:30:24'),(828,'service_section_items','title',66,'en','Vascular surgery Clinic for Patients With Kidney Failure','2021-01-01 21:40:55','2021-01-08 16:29:40'),(829,'service_section_items','content',66,'en','<p>Dialysis for kidney patients requires continuous follow-up in the vascular surgery clinic, where the clinic provides the following services for patients with dialysis, including: (implantation of a permanent dialysis catheter, making simple and complex dialysis connections, implantation of artificial arteries for use in dialysis, and clearing and dissolving clots with dialysis connections We also perform the diagnostic and therapeutic catheterization for dialysis connections with an expansion of the strictures by balloon and use of stents if necessary