-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Measuring levels of chemical components in the body such as blood glucose.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%; text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Measuring the level of enzymes and hormones.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%; text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Measuring the level of electrons, fats and proteins.</span></li>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%; text-align: left;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Measuring antibody level, performing allergic and metabolic tests.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Microorganisms</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">This section helps in detecting microbes such as bacteria or viruses inside the body, as it works on clinical samples such as stool swabs, urine, blood, sputum, cerebrospinal fluid, synovial fluid, potentially infected tissues, and testing for sensitivity to antibiotics.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Blood Diseases</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Blood is one of the most important parts of the body that needs accurate and continuous checks. In this section, blood cell and bone marrow tests are performed to help diagnose anemia, hereditary hemophilia, blood clotting disorders, and leukemia.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">Blood Bank</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">This section applies the highest safety standards in selecting blood donors, preparing blood components and storing. The platelet apheresis service is provided from the donor to the patient, the exchange transfusion service is provided to the patient, and the blood supply to normal patients and patients with extremely complex conditions is provided.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Arial; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 8.0pt; line-height: 107%;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 107%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; li