7:41'),(1816,'testimonials','dr_name',14,'en','Diabetes Doctor','2021-01-04 08:47:41','2021-01-04 08:47:41'),(1817,'testimonials','department',14,'en','Diabetes Clinic','2021-01-04 08:47:41','2021-01-04 08:47:41'),(1818,'community_contents','content',21,'en','<div class=\"middle-paragraph\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<p>Under the guidance of His Excellency, the Director-General of the Ministry of Human Resources and Social Development Branch in the Eastern Province, Mr. Abdulrahman bin Fahd Al-Muqbil- the Social Responsibility Department at the Ministry&rsquo;s <br />branch signed, on Monday 19, 2020, a cooperation agreement with Almoosa Specialist Hospital to launch the &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s Learn&rdquo; initiative. &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s learn&rdquo; aims to provide ( 100) computer devices for the orphans, needy families, and other cases sponsored by the Ministry in the Eastern Province to ensure the possibility of completing their educational journey remotely.</p>\n<p>ASH provided the devices at a financial cost of about (130,000) thousand SR, believing in their social responsibility and their national duty towards the individuals, and the Social Responsibility<br />Department was keen to provide these devices to male and female beneficiaries to facilitate their distance learning process</p>\n</div>\n</div>','2021-01-04 11:11:59','2021-01-04 11:11:59'),(1819,'community_contents','title',26,'en','Objectives','2021-01-04 11:58:33','2021-02-10 16:08:30'),(1820,'community_contents','content',26,'en','<p>We aspire to support and encourage young talents, highlighting local artists, immortalizing their works, integrating art with therapy and society, and raising the artistic taste of the community by visually satisfying them with paintings and pictures of high quality and cultural value.</p>','2021-01-04 11:58:33','2021-02-10 18:01:12'),(1821,'community_contents','title',27,'en','AHSA RUN MARATHON Video','2021-01-04 12:05:49','2021-01-04 12:05:49'),(1822,'community_contents','title',28,'en','A Smile of Hope','2021-01-04 12:10:51','2021-01-04 12:10:51'),(1823,'community_contents','content',28,'en','<p>We allocated a budget to treat 30 children in cooperation with the Al-Ber Association, where the Al-Ber Association nominated cases and evaluated them financially, while Almoosa Specialist Hospital evaluated the cases from the health point of view, and indeed we have succeeded so far in treating 4 children, and we are continuing to treat the rest of the cases.</p>','2021-01-04 12:10:51','2021-03-11 13:27:49'),(1824,'community_contents','content',29,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">These community initiatives are a living model that helps people with special needs integrate with others, and they aim to provide an opportunity for people with special needs to integrate into life and interact with others, as it is a good space for self-entertainment and hobbies.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">In addition, parks are a center of learning and provide the opportunity for children to get to know their peers with special needs closely, which helps the community to get rid of misconceptions about the abilities of children with special needs.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\"><strong>The \"We Play Together\" park is located in the Al-Faisal neighborhood in Al-Mubarraz, on an area of ​​more than 2,200 square meters, to include more than 12 specialized games for children with special sensory and physical needs.</strong></span></p>','2021-01-04 12:17:05','2021-01-08 12:44:46'),(1825,'community_contents','title',31,'en','Everyone Is a Paramedic Initiative','2021-01-04 12:28:21','2021-01-04 12:28:21'),(1826,'community_contents','content',31,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">The first moments of the accidents and fractures are determining moments in the life of the injured person, what happens later and complications and their size depends on the correctness of dealing with those around him in the first moments.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Therefore, and based on our responsibilities in educating the community and enhancing preparedness for emergencies and accidents, we launched the \"Paramedic in Every School\" initiative, which aims to rehabilitate and train teachers in CPR and first aid to save students and how to behave well in emergency incidents.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Hundreds of teachers registered in Al-Ahsaa, received training on how to perform first aid and pulmonary resuscitation, and obtained a certificate proving that they had the training and their full ability to perform first aid and cardiopulmonary resuscitation in case of emergency and difficult accidents that require speed of intuition and taking the right decision.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Later, we collaborated with content creator Omar Farouk to spread the initiative by filming an episode titled \"I am a nurse\" to highlight the importance of the nursing profession and the importance of learning the first aid course to save lives and deal with serious cases in the right way, while the episode received more than 4 million views. After training more than 3000 people for free, in first aid skills and proper medical intervention.</span></p>','2021-01-04 12:28:21','2021-01-08 12:40:31'),(1827,'community_contents','title',33,'en','PARAMEDIC IN EACH SCHOOL Video','2021-01-04 12:29:42','2021-01-04 12:29:42'),(1828,'community_contents','content',34,'en','<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The Chairman of the Board of Directors of Al-Mousa Hospital, Mr. Malik bin Abdulaziz Al-Musa, noted the importance of embodying ways of cooperation, interdependence and solidarity between the private sector, government sectors and community members. The Director of Marketing and Community Partnerships Sarah Bint Abdulaziz Al-Musa gave a speech in which she mentioned the importance of activating such national initiatives that are presented. For community members and contribute to advancing development and continuing education for children of low-income families.</span></p>','2021-01-04 12:54:55','2021-01-04 12:54:55'),(1829,'community_contents','content',35,'en','<p>He added: We are confident that the initiative will achieve a positive impact and will contribute to meeting the necessary needs for them and alleviating their suffering, and we all hope to increase the number of these specific initiatives and projects that aim to achieve the goals of our dear vision 2030.</p>','2021-01-04 12:57:03','2021-02-01 19:15:55'),(1830,'community_contents','title',36,'en','To Learn Initiative','2021-01-04 12:58:26','2021-01-04 12:58:26'),(1831,'community_contents','content',36,'en','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 115%;\">Al-Obaid thanked the success partners, headed by Mrs. Sarah Al-Moosa, and the Social Responsibility Working Group, both: Ms. Samia Salem, Ms. Somaia Al-Dossary, and all those who contributed to the success of this initiative.</span></p>','2021-01-04 12:58:26','2021-01-04 12:58:26'),(1832,'service_sections','title',105,'en','Orthopedic and joint and trauma surgeries','2021-01-04 15:23:20','2021-01-04 15:23:20'),(1833,'service_section_items','content',107,'